## ⚠ Enforcement asymmetry — the guards that DON'T bind you
The three `.claude/hooks/*.mjs` PreToolUse guards (cross-repo writes, lane-authoring, gate-ladder) are
**Claude Code harness registrations. They do NOT bind a Codex / non-Claude lane** — you never load
them. **What binds you is THIS prose + the `.githooks/pre-commit` hook** (`core.hooksPath=.githooks`),
which runs at commit time regardless of harness and blocks a commit that has no valid lane declaration
or stages out-of-scope paths. Treat these rules as binding on your honor AND enforced at the commit.
Full model: `PORTABILITY.md`.

## Multi-writer checkout — surgical staging only
If more than one agent lane writes this checkout, these rules bind **EVERY** agent. **The canonical
text is `core/OPERATE.md` § Multi-writer checkout** — the hard prohibitions are repeated here because
violating one is unrecoverable, but that section governs.

1. **NEVER blanket-stage:** no `git add -A`, `git add .`, or `git commit -a`. Stage explicit paths
   your task touched — nothing else.
2. **Verify before every commit:** run `git status`; every staged file must belong to YOUR task.
   Unexplained dirty files are the other lane's in-flight work — never stage, stash, revert, or edit
   them. If YOUR task needs a file the other lane has dirtied, STOP and ask the Owner.
3. **Substantial concurrent work → a private worktree** (never inside the shared checkout). Commit
   early and often there: `/tmp` is purged on reboot, and only commits survive it.
4. **Merge + test in the worktree, never in the shared checkout:** merge the shared branch INTO your
   worktree, install deps there (**`npm ci`** if the merge touched the lockfile), run the **full
   `npm test`** THERE, and only then land the merge.
5. **Dependency changes are single-lane.** A lockfile CONFLICT → keep the conflicted lockfile and run
   `npm install` (it resolves the markers, preserving pins); never hand-merge or delete-and-regenerate.
6. **Pushing `{{DEPLOY_BRANCH}}` {{DEPLOY_EFFECT}}.** Only a T0 docs-only push is GO-free; ANY push
   containing code — and any T1–T3 push — needs the Owner's push-GO first. A push ships the WHOLE
   branch: before any push, check `git log {{DEPLOY_REMOTE_REF}}..HEAD` for ungated work from ANY lane.

## Before the first code write
Declare the lane in `.claude/task-lane.json` (session id + kebab task id + exactly one route:
`lane` · `in-thread` · `exempt`). For the Claude lane the PreToolUse hook blocks an undeclared write;
**for you, the `pre-commit` hook blocks an undeclared code COMMIT** (fail-closed). Details:
`core/OPERATE.md` § Optional build lanes, `core/BINDINGS.md` § Tool bindings.
